transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hey John, uh, I just called to check on the status of a delivery.

Speaker 1: I've never received an email or anything like that, so...

Speaker 2: Yeah, I need your name and zip code, please.

Speaker 1: Uh, my name is Pat, last name's Cutrone, C-U-T-R-O-N-E.

Speaker 2: Need some zip?

Speaker 1: Yes, please.

Speaker 2: 33706.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Second Street in Treasure Island, Florida?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, it will be shipping out either today or tomorrow, sir.

Speaker 1: Yesterday with the snowstorms, our pharmacies in Kentucky, they had real limited hours, so they weren't able to get all the orders out.

Speaker 2: Well, I understand.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no, no, I know, I'm just telling you the status.

Speaker 2: But you are all set, it is good to go, it is set to ship, it just hasn't quite shipped.

Speaker 1: But you will get an email sent to the PJC1444 Gmail when it ships.

Speaker 2: Okay, I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Of course, sir, hope you have a good one.

Speaker 2: You too, thanks.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
